datasets.name: fc2d4844
datasets.query:
WITH raw_history AS (
    SELECT
        f.*,
        CASE 
            WHEN QueryRuntimeSeconds >= CAST(:long_running_seconds_treshold AS FLOAT) 
            THEN 'Long Running' 
            ELSE 'Short Running' 
        END AS LongRunningQueryFlag,
        CASE 
            WHEN QueryRuntimeSeconds >= CAST(:long_running_seconds_treshold AS FLOAT) 
            THEN 1 
            ELSE 0 
        END AS Calc_LongRunningQueryFlag
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_query_history f
    WHERE 
        f.warehouse_id IN (
            SELECT DISTINCT warehouse_id 
            FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_current AS c
            WHERE lower(c.warehouse_id) = lower(:warehouse_id)
        )
        AND start_time BETWEEN CAST(:start_range AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_range AS TIMESTAMP)
),

px_all AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT
        sku_name,
        pricing.default AS unit_price,
        CAST(unit_price AS DECIMAL(10,3)) AS sku_price
    FROM system.billing.list_prices 
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY sku_name ORDER BY price_start_time DESC) = 1
),

history AS (
    SELECT *,
        SUM(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation) OVER () AS TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse,
        SUM(COALESCE(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation, 0)) OVER (PARTITION BY statement_text) AS TotalStatementTextTimeUsed,
        CASE 
            WHEN TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse = 0 THEN NULL 
            ELSE TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation / TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse 
        END AS ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery
    FROM raw_history
),

filtered_warehouse_usage AS (
    WITH trimmed_usage AS (
        SELECT 
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, usage_start_time, CAST(:start_range AS TIMESTAMP)) AS seconds_before_start_range,
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, usage_start_time, usage_end_time) AS full_start_range_length,
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, GREATEST(CAST(:start_range AS TIMESTAMP), usage_start_time), usage_end_time) AS seconds_remaining_in_original_start_range,
            GREATEST(CAST(:start_range AS TIMESTAMP), usage_start_time) AS trimmed_start_time,
            LEAST(CAST(:end_range AS TIMESTAMP), usage_end_time) AS trimmed_end_time,
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, LEAST(CAST(:end_range AS TIMESTAMP), usage_end_time), usage_end_time) AS seconds_after_end_range,
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, usage_start_time, usage_end_time) AS full_end_range_length,
            CASE 
                WHEN full_start_range_length > 0 
                THEN COALESCE((full_start_range_length - seconds_before_start_range) / full_start_range_length, 0) 
                ELSE NULL 
            END AS StartTrimProportion,
            CASE 
                WHEN full_end_range_length > 0 
                THEN COALESCE((full_end_range_length - seconds_after_end_range) / full_end_range_length, 0) 
                ELSE NULL 
            END AS EndTrimProportion,
            COALESCE(EndTrimProportion, StartTrimProportion, 1) AS TrimProportion,
            u.usage_start_time,
            u.usage_end_time,
            u.usage_quantity AS dbus,
            u.warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
            (CAST(px.sku_price AS FLOAT) * (1 - CAST(:dbsql_discount AS FLOAT)) * dbus) AS UsageDollars
        FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_usage AS u
        INNER JOIN px_all AS px 
            ON px.sku_name = u.sku_name
        WHERE 
            (u.warehouse_id = :warehouse_id 

            OR u.warehouse_id IN (
                SELECT DISTINCT warehouse_id 
                FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_current AS c
                WHERE lower(c.warehouse_name) = lower(:warehouse_id)
            )
            )
            AND usage_unit = 'DBU'
            AND (
                (usage_start_time BETWEEN CAST(:start_range AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_range AS TIMESTAMP))
                OR (usage_end_time BETWEEN CAST(:start_range AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_range AS TIMESTAMP))
            )
    )
    SELECT 
        warehouse_id,
        SUM(dbus * TrimProportion) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs,
        SUM(UsageDollars * TrimProportion) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars
    FROM trimmed_usage
    GROUP BY warehouse_id
),

warehouse_average_ratio_metrics AS (
    SELECT 
        warehouse_id,
        COALESCE(AVG(CAST(CPUTotalExecutionTime AS FLOAT)) / AVG(CAST(QueryRuntimeSeconds AS FLOAT)), 0) AS WarehouseAvgTaskSkewRatio,
        COALESCE(MAX(CPUTotalExecutionTime) / MAX(QueryRuntimeSeconds), 0) AS WarehouseMaxTaskSkewRatio,
        AVG(ReadDataAmountInGB) AS WarehouseAvgReadDataInGBPerQuery,
        STDDEV(ReadDataAmountInGB) AS WarehouseStdReadDataInGBPerQuery,
        AVG(read_io_cache_percent) AS WarehouseAvgDeltaCachePercent,
        STDDEV(read_io_cache_percent) AS WarehouseStdDeltaCachePercent,
        AVG(spilled_local_bytes) AS WarehouseAvgDiskSpillAmount,
        STDDEV(spilled_local_bytes) AS WarehouseStdDiskSpillAmount
    FROM history
    WHERE CPUTotalExecutionTime > 0 AND ReadDataAmountInGB > 0
    AND execution_status NOT IN ('FAILED')
    GROUP BY warehouse_id
),

query_level_intel_metrics AS (
    SELECT qh.*,
        w.WarehouseAvgTaskSkewRatio AS WarehouseAvgTaskToExecutionTimeRatio,
        CASE 
            WHEN CPUTotalExecutionTime > 0 
            AND ReadDataAmountInGB > 0 
            AND execution_status NOT IN ('FAILED')
            THEN qh.QueryRuntimeSeconds / (qh.CPUTotalExecutionTime / w.WarehouseAvgTaskSkewRatio)
            ELSE NULL
        END AS QueryEfficiencyRatio,
        w.WarehouseAvgReadDataInGBPerQuery,
        w.WarehouseStdReadDataInGBPerQuery,
        w.WarehouseAvgDeltaCachePercent,
        w.WarehouseStdDeltaCachePercent,
        w.WarehouseAvgDiskSpillAmount,
        w.WarehouseStdDiskSpillAmount,
        u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars,
        (u.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars * ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery) AS AllocatedQueryCostByTime
    FROM history AS qh
    LEFT JOIN warehouse_average_ratio_metrics AS w ON w.warehouse_id = qh.warehouse_id
    LEFT JOIN filtered_warehouse_usage AS u ON u.warehouse_id = qh.warehouse_id
),

zscores AS (
    SELECT 
        *,
        AVG(QueryEfficiencyRatio) OVER () AS WarehouseAvgQueryEfficiencyRatio,
        (spilled_local_bytes - WarehouseAvgDiskSpillAmount) / NULLIF(WarehouseStdDiskSpillAmount, 0) AS SpillAmountZScore,
        (read_io_cache_percent - WarehouseAvgDeltaCachePercent) / NULLIF(WarehouseStdDeltaCachePercent, 0) AS CachePercentZScore,
        (ReadDataAmountInGB - WarehouseAvgReadDataInGBPerQuery) / NULLIF(WarehouseStdReadDataInGBPerQuery, 0) AS DataVolumeZScore
        --PERCENTILE_CONT(0.5) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY QueryRuntimeSeconds) OVER () AS QueryRuntime_P50,
        --PERCENTILE_CONT(0.9) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY QueryRuntimeSeconds) OVER () AS QueryRuntime_P90,
        --PERCENTILE_CONT(0.95) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY QueryRuntimeSeconds) OVER () AS QueryRuntime_P95,
        --PERCENTILE_CONT(0.99) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY QueryRuntimeSeconds) OVER () AS QueryRuntime_P99,
        --PERCENTILE_CONT(0.5) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY QueueQueryTime) OVER () AS QueryQueueTime_P50,
        --PERCENTILE_CONT(0.9) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY QueueQueryTime) OVER () AS QueryQueueTime_P90,
        --PERCENTILE_CONT(0.95) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY QueueQueryTime) OVER () AS QueryQueueTime_P95,
        --PERCENTILE_CONT(0.99) WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY QueueQueryTime) OVER () AS QueryQueueTime_P99
    FROM query_level_intel_metrics
)

SELECT 
    z.*,
    CASE 
        WHEN DataVolumeZScore > CASE WHEN LENGTH(CAST(:data_volume_min_z_score AS FLOAT)) > 1 THEN CAST(:data_volume_min_z_score AS FLOAT) ELSE 1 END 
        THEN 'High Relative Volume Read' 
        ELSE 'Not High Relative Volume' 
    END AS HighDataVolumeFlag,
    CASE 
        WHEN DataVolumeZScore > CASE WHEN LENGTH(CAST(:data_volume_min_z_score AS FLOAT)) > 1 THEN CAST(:data_volume_min_z_score AS FLOAT) ELSE 1 END 
        THEN 1 
        ELSE 0 
    END AS Calc_HighDataVolumeFlag,
    (Calc_HasSpillFlag + Calc_ReadDataFlag + Calc_UsedWorkerTasksFlag + Calc_LongRunningQueryFlag + Calc_HighDataVolumeFlag
    + COALESCE(SpillAmountZScore, 0) + COALESCE(DataVolumeZScore, 0)) AS ProblemQueryMetric,
    CASE 
        WHEN LENGTH(raw_tagged) >= 1 THEN raw_tagged 
        ELSE 'Untagged' 
    END AS QueryTag,
    -- Warehouse-level event info
    current_warehouses.action_name,
current_warehouses.warehouse_name,
current_warehouses.warehouse_type,
current_warehouses.auto_stop_mins,
current_warehouses.warehouse_size,
current_warehouses.min_cluster_scaling,
current_warehouses.max_cluster_scaing,
current_warehouses.warehouse_channel,
current_warehouses.warehouse_editor_user,
current_warehouses.ChangeRank,
current_warehouses.RecencyRank,
current_warehouses.IsDeleted,
current_warehouses.warehouse_creator,
current_warehouses.warehouse_latest_editor,
current_warehouses.IsDeletedCurrently,
TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, :start_range, :end_range) AS total_window_seconds
FROM zscores AS z
LEFT JOIN main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_current AS current_warehouses ON current_warehouses.warehouse_id = z.warehouse_id

datasets.name: 36bb7aba
datasets.query:
-- Most recent warehouse config in selected time period
WITH warehouse_snapshot AS (
    SELECT * 
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_scd 
    WHERE action_name IN ('createWarehouse', 'createEndpoint', 'editWarehouse', 'editEndpoint')
    AND event_time <= CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP)
    AND (
        warehouse_id = :warehouse_id
    )
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY account_id, workspace_id, warehouse_id ORDER BY event_time DESC) = 1
),


raw_scaling AS (
    SELECT 
        DATE_TRUNC('MINUTE', w.event_time) AS event_minute,
        MAX(w.cluster_count) AS clusters,
        MAX(w.warehouse_id) AS warehouse_id
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_scaling_events w
    INNER JOIN warehouse_snapshot c 
        ON w.warehouse_id = c.warehouse_id
    WHERE w.event_time BETWEEN CAST(:start_time AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP)
    AND event_type IN ('RUNNING', 'SCALED_UP', 'SCALED_DOWN', 'STOPPED')
    GROUP BY DATE_TRUNC('MINUTE', w.event_time)
    ORDER BY event_minute
),

full_series AS (
SELECT explode(sequence((SELECT MIN(event_minute) FROM raw_scaling), (SELECT MAX(event_minute) FROM raw_scaling), INTERVAL 1 MINUTE)) AS minuteChunk
),


filled_in_series AS (
    SELECT 
        spine.minuteChunk AS event_minute,
        MAX(s2.clusters) AS NumberOfClustersOn,
        MAX(s2.warehouse_id) AS warehouse_id
    FROM full_series AS spine
    LEFT JOIN raw_scaling AS s2 
        ON DATE_TRUNC('MINUTE', s2.event_minute) = spine.minuteChunk
    GROUP BY spine.minuteChunk
    ORDER BY event_minute
),

final_scale AS (
SELECT event_minute,
LAST_VALUE(NumberOfClustersOn, true) OVER (ORDER BY event_minute) AS NumberOfClustersOn,
LAST_VALUE(w.warehouse_id, true) OVER (ORDER BY event_minute)  AS warehouse_id
 FROM filled_in_series  w
 ORDER BY warehouse_id, event_minute
)

SELECT 
f.*,
warehouse_channel,
warehouse_size,
min_cluster_scaling AS warehouse_min_clusters,
max_cluster_scaing AS warehouse_max_clusters,
auto_stop_mins AS warehouse_auto_stop_min
FROM final_scale AS f
LEFT JOIN warehouse_snapshot c ON f.warehouse_id = c.warehouse_id

datasets.name: 871b75c8
datasets.query:
WITH warehouse_snapshot AS (
    SELECT * 
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_current w
    WHERE (
        lower(w.warehouse_id) = lower(:warehouse_id)
    )
    LIMIT 1
), 

px_all AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT
        sku_name,
        pricing.default AS unit_price,
        CAST(unit_price AS DECIMAL(10,3)) AS sku_price
    FROM system.billing.list_prices 
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY sku_name ORDER BY price_start_time DESC) = 1
),

raw_history AS (
    SELECT * 
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_query_history f
    WHERE 
    f.warehouse_id IN  (
            SELECT DISTINCT warehouse_id FROM warehouse_snapshot
        )
    AND start_time >= CAST(:start_time AS TIMESTAMP) 
    AND end_time <= CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP) 
    AND QueryRuntimeSeconds > 0
    AND statement_type IS NOT NULL
),

history AS (
    SELECT *,
        SUM(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation) OVER () AS TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse,
        SUM(COALESCE(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation, 0)) OVER (PARTITION BY statement_text) AS TotalStatementTextTimeUsed,
        CASE 
            WHEN TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse = 0 THEN NULL 
            ELSE TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation / TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse 
        END AS ProportionOfWarehouseTimeUsedByQuery
    FROM raw_history
),

filtered_warehouse_usage AS (
    WITH trimmed_usage AS (
        SELECT 
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, usage_start_time, CAST(:start_time AS TIMESTAMP)) AS seconds_before_start_range,
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, usage_start_time, usage_end_time) AS full_start_range_length,
            full_start_range_length - seconds_before_start_range AS seconds_remaining_in_original_start_range,
            GREATEST(CAST(:start_time AS TIMESTAMP), usage_start_time) AS trimmed_start_time,
            LEAST(CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP), usage_end_time) AS trimmed_end_time,
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP), usage_end_time) AS seconds_after_end_range,
            TIMESTAMPDIFF(SECOND, usage_start_time, usage_end_time) AS full_end_range_length,
            full_end_range_length - seconds_after_end_range AS seconds_remaining_in_original_end_range,

            CASE 
                WHEN seconds_before_start_range > 0 
                THEN COALESCE((full_start_range_length - seconds_before_start_range) / full_start_range_length, 0) 
                ELSE NULL 
            END AS StartTrimProportion,
            CASE 
                WHEN seconds_after_end_range > 0 
                THEN COALESCE((full_start_range_length - seconds_after_end_range) / full_start_range_length, 0) 
                ELSE NULL 
            END AS EndTrimProportion,
            COALESCE(EndTrimProportion, StartTrimProportion, 1) AS TrimProportion,
            u.usage_start_time,
            u.usage_end_time,
            u.usage_quantity AS dbus,
            u.warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
            (CAST(px.sku_price AS FLOAT) * (1 - CAST(:dbsql_discount AS FLOAT)) * dbus) AS UsageDollars
        FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_usage AS u
        INNER JOIN px_all AS px 
            ON px.sku_name = u.sku_name
        WHERE 
            (u.warehouse_id = :warehouse_id 
            OR EXISTS (
                SELECT warehouse_id 
                FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_current AS c
                WHERE c.warehouse_id = u.warehouse_id AND warehouse_name = :warehouse_id
            ))
            AND usage_unit = 'DBU'
            AND (
                usage_start_time BETWEEN CAST(:start_time AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP)
                OR usage_end_time BETWEEN CAST(:start_time AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP)
            )
    )
    SELECT 
        u. warehouse_id,
        SUM(u.dbus * TrimProportion) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs,
        SUM(u.UsageDollars * TrimProportion) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars
    FROM trimmed_usage AS u
    GROUP BY warehouse_id
),

history_with_pricing AS (
    SELECT 
        h1.*,
        wh.Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs, 
        wh.Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars
    FROM history AS h1
    LEFT JOIN filtered_warehouse_usage AS wh 
        ON h1.warehouse_id = wh.warehouse_id
),

query_proportion_agg AS (
    SELECT 
        SHA2(REGEXP_REPLACE(REGEXP_REPLACE(REGEXP_REPLACE(statement_text, '/\\*.*?\\*/', ''), '(--[^\\n]*)', ''), ' ', ''), 256) AS query_signature,
        MAX(statement_text) AS statement_text,
        MAX(statement_type) AS statetment_type,
        MAX(raw_tagged) AS raw_tagged,
        MAX(dbt_app) AS dbt_app,
        MAX(dbt_node_id) AS dbt_node_id,
        MAX(dbt_profile_name) AS dbt_profile_id,
        MAX(dbt_target_name) AS dbt_target_name,
        MAX(dbt_version) AS dbt_version,
        MAX(IsDBTQuery) AS IsDBTQuery,
        FIRST(parsed_dbt_comment) AS parsed_dbt_comment,
        COUNT(statement_id) AS NumberOfExecutions,
        AVG(QueryRuntimeSeconds) AS AvgRuntimeInSeconds,
        MAX(TotalUsedTimeInWarehouse) AS TotalWarehouseTimeUsed,
        MAX(Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs,
        MAX(Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars) AS Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars,
        SUM(TotalResourceTimeUsedForAllocation) AS TotalStatementTimeUsed,
        ARRAY_DISTINCT(COLLECT_LIST(NAMED_STRUCT('user', executed_by, 'execution_count', 
            (SELECT COUNT(statement_id) FROM history AS in_hist 
             WHERE in_hist.executed_by = u.executed_by AND in_hist.statement_text = u.statement_text)
        ))) AS UserRunCounts
    FROM history_with_pricing AS u
    GROUP BY query_signature
),

statement_attribution AS (
    SELECT 
        a.*,
        CASE 
            WHEN TotalWarehouseTimeUsed = 0 THEN NULL 
            ELSE TotalStatementTimeUsed / TotalWarehouseTimeUsed 
        END AS StatementTaskTimeProportion,
        Total_Warehouse_Period_Dollars * StatementTaskTimeProportion AS StatementAllocatedDollars,
        Total_Warehouse_Period_DBUs * StatementTaskTimeProportion AS StatementAllocatedDBUs
    FROM query_proportion_agg a
),

statement_rollup_cumulative_sum AS (
    SELECT 
        *,
        SUM(StatementTaskTimeProportion) OVER (ORDER BY StatementTaskTimeProportion DESC) AS CumulativeProportionOfWarehouseTime
    FROM statement_attribution
),

ranked_query_costs AS (
    SELECT 
        s.*,
        StatementTaskTimeProportion * 100 AS StatementWarehouseTimePercentage,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY StatementTaskTimeProportion DESC) AS QueryCostRank,
        CASE 
            WHEN LENGTH(raw_tagged) >= 1 THEN raw_tagged 
            ELSE 'Untagged' 
        END AS QueryTag,
        CASE 
            WHEN s.CumulativeProportionOfWarehouseTime <= CAST(:query_pareto AS FLOAT) 
            THEN s.statement_text 
            ELSE 'Remaining Long Tail of Queries' 
        END AS QueryProportionParetoFlag
    FROM statement_rollup_cumulative_sum s
    ORDER BY CumulativeProportionOfWarehouseTime
)

SELECT 
    *,
    CASE 
        WHEN QueryCostRank <= :top_n 
        THEN 'Top N Query' 
        ELSE 'Remaining Queries' 
    END AS TopNFilter
FROM ranked_query_costs
ORDER BY QueryCostRank

datasets.name: fb74d1e7
datasets.query:
WITH with_delete_flag AS (
    SELECT * 
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_current
),

px_all AS (
    SELECT DISTINCT
        sku_name,
        pricing.default AS unit_price,
        CAST(unit_price AS DECIMAL(10,3)) AS sku_price
    FROM system.billing.list_prices 
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY sku_name ORDER BY price_start_time DESC) = 1
),

-- Active Warehouse Metadata
clean_usage AS (
    SELECT 
        w.*,
        usage_date, 
        usage_quantity AS DBUs,
        (CAST(px.sku_price AS FLOAT) * (1 - CAST(:dbsql_discount AS FLOAT)) * usage_quantity) AS UsageDollars,
        custom_tags
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_usage AS u
    INNER JOIN px_all AS px 
        ON px.sku_name = u.sku_name
    INNER JOIN with_delete_flag AS w 
        ON usage_metadata.warehouse_id = w.warehouse_id
    WHERE warehouse_name IS NOT NULL
    AND usage_date BETWEEN CAST(:start_date AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_date AS TIMESTAMP)
),

warehouse_ranks AS (
    SELECT 
        account_id, 
        workspace_id, 
        warehouse_id,
        SUM(UsageDollars) AS total_warehouse_usage_in_period,
        DENSE_RANK() OVER (ORDER BY SUM(UsageDollars) DESC) AS WarehouseUsageTopNRank
    FROM clean_usage
    GROUP BY account_id, workspace_id, warehouse_id
)

SELECT 
    u.*,
    SHA2(warehouse_name, 256) AS masked_warehouse_name,
    SHA2(warehouse_creator, 256) AS masked_warehouse_creator,
    r.WarehouseUsageTopNRank
FROM clean_usage AS u 
INNER JOIN warehouse_ranks AS r 
    ON u.warehouse_id = r.warehouse_id 
    AND u.account_id = r.account_id 
    AND u.workspace_id = r.workspace_id

datasets.name: 547c0662
datasets.query:
WITH warehouse_snapshot AS (
    SELECT * 
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_current w
    WHERE (
        lower(w.warehouse_id) = lower(:warehouse_id)
    )
    LIMIT 1
), 

query_queuing_history AS (
    SELECT 
        statement_id,
        warehouse_id AS warehouse_id,
        QueryRuntimeSeconds*1000 AS total_duration_ms,
        COALESCE(QueueQueryTime*1000, 0) AS queueing_ms, -- Queue time is the total of waiting_at_capacity and waiting_for_compute in the MV
        ExecutionQueryTime*1000 AS execution_duration_ms,
        start_time AS query_start_timestamp,
        TIMESTAMPADD(MILLISECOND, queueing_ms, query_start_timestamp) AS queuing_end_timestamp,
        CASE WHEN queueing_ms > 0 THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS IsQueued,
        end_time AS query_end_timestamp,
        DATE_TRUNC('SECOND', query_start_timestamp) AS query_start_second,
        DATE_TRUNC('SECOND', queuing_end_timestamp) AS query_queue_end_second
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_query_history qh
    WHERE qh.start_time BETWEEN CAST(:start_time AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP)
    AND qh.warehouse_id IN ( SELECT DISTINCT warehouse_id FROM warehouse_snapshot )
),

full_series AS (
SELECT explode(sequence((SELECT date_trunc('SECOND', MIN(query_start_timestamp)) FROM query_queuing_history), (SELECT date_trunc('SECOND', MAX(query_end_timestamp)) FROM query_queuing_history), INTERVAL 1 SECOND)) AS secondChunk
),

queuing_details AS (
    SELECT 
        spine.secondChunk AS second_chunk, 
        -- IsQueued during window flag
        CASE 
            WHEN (spine.secondChunk >= DATE_TRUNC('SECOND', q.query_start_timestamp)
                  AND spine.secondChunk <= q.queuing_end_timestamp) 
                 AND q.IsQueued = 1
            THEN 1 ELSE 0 
        END AS IsQueuedDuringSecond,
        -- Peak running
        CASE 
            WHEN (spine.secondChunk >= DATE_TRUNC('SECOND', q.queuing_end_timestamp)
                  AND spine.secondChunk <= q.query_end_timestamp)
            THEN 1 ELSE 0 
        END AS IsRunningDuringSecond,   
        q.query_start_timestamp, 
        q.queuing_end_timestamp, 
        q.query_end_timestamp, 
        q.statement_id
    FROM full_series AS spine
    LEFT JOIN query_queuing_history AS q 
        ON (spine.secondChunk >= DATE_TRUNC('SECOND', q.query_start_timestamp)
            AND spine.secondChunk <= q.query_end_timestamp)
    WHERE q.statement_id IS NOT NULL
),

second_level_queuing AS (
    SELECT
        DATE_TRUNC('SECOND', second_chunk) AS second_int, 
        SUM(IsQueuedDuringSecond) AS QueuedCount, 
        SUM(IsRunningDuringSecond) AS RunningCount
    FROM queuing_details
    GROUP BY DATE_TRUNC('SECOND', second_chunk)
    ORDER BY second_int
)

SELECT 
    DATE_ADD(MINUTE, FLOOR(EXTRACT(MINUTE FROM second_int) / 5) * 5 - EXTRACT(MINUTE FROM second_int), DATE_TRUNC('MINUTE', second_int)) AS five_min_interval,
    MAX(RunningCount) AS PeakRunning,
    MAX(QueuedCount) AS PeakQueued
FROM second_level_queuing
GROUP BY five_min_interval
ORDER BY five_min_interval

datasets.name: e139c435
datasets.query:
-- Most recent warehouse config in selected time period

WITH raw_scaling AS (
    SELECT 
        DATE_TRUNC('MINUTE', w.event_time) AS event_minute,
        MAX(w.cluster_count) AS clusters,
        MAX(w.warehouse_id) AS warehouse_id
    FROM main.dbsql_warehouse_advisor.warehouse_scaling_events w
    WHERE 
    warehouse_id = :warehouse_id
    AND w.event_time BETWEEN CAST(:start_time AS TIMESTAMP) AND CAST(:end_time AS TIMESTAMP)
    AND event_type IN ('RUNNING', 'SCALED_UP', 'SCALED_DOWN', 'STOPPED')
    GROUP BY DATE_TRUNC('MINUTE', w.event_time)
    ORDER BY event_minute
),

full_series AS (
    SELECT explode(sequence((SELECT MIN(event_minute) FROM raw_scaling), (SELECT MAX(event_minute) FROM raw_scaling), INTERVAL 1 MINUTE)) AS minuteChunk
),

filled_in_series AS (
    SELECT 
        spine.minuteChunk AS event_minute,
        MAX(s2.clusters) AS NumberOfClustersOn,
        MAX(s2.warehouse_id) AS warehouse_id
    FROM full_series AS spine
    LEFT JOIN raw_scaling AS s2 
        ON DATE_TRUNC('MINUTE', s2.event_minute) = spine.minuteChunk
    GROUP BY spine.minuteChunk
    ORDER BY event_minute
),

final_scale AS (
    SELECT event_minute,
    LAST_VALUE(NumberOfClustersOn, true) OVER (ORDER BY event_minute) AS NumberOfClustersOn,
    LAST_VALUE(w.warehouse_id, true) OVER (ORDER BY event_minute)  AS warehouse_id
    FROM filled_in_series  w
    ORDER BY warehouse_id, event_minute
)

-- Daily Aggregation
SELECT 
    DATE_TRUNC('DAY', event_minute) AS event_day,
    NumberOfClustersOn,
    COUNT(*) AS total_minutes
FROM final_scale
GROUP BY event_day, NumberOfClustersOn
ORDER BY event_day, NumberOfClustersOn

### Query Performance Detail
This section drills into details of identifying root causes of poorly performing warehouses down to the query bottlenecks such as spill, high data volume, and long running queries.

widget.name: d1c59f1c
widget.textbox_spec:
## Warehouse Performance - Queuing Metrics (Peak Queued Over Time)
Peak Queuing shows how many queries get queued before running in a given time window. The MAX peak queued queries in a time window helps show how much more concurrency scaling the warehouse might need to not require queuing. 
##### Best Practices: 
Just because there is queuing, does not mean you need to scale up your warehouse. Always scale your warehouses based on the SLA metrics first. If queries are being queued and you still meet your SLA, there is no value in increases concurrency scaling of the warehouse.

widget.name: 916d7ade
widget.textbox_spec:
# DBSQL Warehouse Advisor

## Sections
1. Warehouse General Intel - show basic billing usage and cost metrics for a warehouse (dbus, $, over time)
2. Warehouse Scaling Intel - shows basic scaling metrics per warehouse (scaling history, avg scale (weighted))
3. Performance Advisor - Show common query history metrics such as runtime, queue time, peak queuing, failure rate, cache %, etc., identify inefficient queries with skew/spill indicators
4. Query Statement Level Resource Allocation Advisor - Identify and allocate warehouse total used time by statement and query (optionally include and aggregate by TAG)

widget.name: 895515b7
widget.textbox_spec:
## Section 3: Query Performance Analysis
-----
This section helps dive into warehouse performance to understand how well the warehouse is performing against SLAs, identifying bottlenecks, as well as queries that are taking up the majority of the resources.

-----
## Key Performance KPIs
This section tracks 3 core KPIS: 

1. Query Runtime (P50, 95,99) - The total runtime (wall clock of a query) - including queueing time
2. Queuing Count (P50,95,99) & Time - The maximum amount of queries in the queue at a given window of time.
3. Queries Spilling to Disk & GBs spilled to disk (P50, 95, 99) - This is the frequency and volume of data spilled to disk to help track warehouse size limits to a query. 
4. GBs Read & Written - This is the amount of data read and written by queries (P50, 95, 99, 100). This is a metric to help understand directionally what cluster size should be chosen.

-----
This section helps to allocate query runtime cost across the warehouse down to the query level. The query costs are aggregated at the "query signature" level, which is a unique SQL statement (excluding comments) executed. This is to account for multiple execution and users executing the same query.

widget.textbox_spec:
## Warehouse Performance - Query Runtime SLAs
Query runtime helps identify if your warehouse is meeting your SLAs. The runtime is generally controlled by the size of the warehouse but also influenced by how long queries are spent queued. So if your queries are running slower than your desired SLA, try increasing the warehouse T-shirt size and using the below visual to see if queries are queuing too often.

##### Best Practices: 
The below visuals show overall P95, 99, as well the as P99/95 for each segment of time within the overall selected window. To use this, focus on the overall SLA. If you are NOT meeting your SLA, then you either need to make the warehouse larger or increase concurrency. If your queries runtimes are taking too long and queries are NOT spending an extensive amount of time queuing, then you likely need a bigger warehouse to run the query faster. If your queuing is high, but your average query runtimes are fine, then you likely need to increase concurrency. Lastly, you can also monitor your query spilling (both frequency and amount) to also use as a clear indicator that your warehouse can be larger to get better performance.  If you are meeting your SLA - you can either do nothing or even make the warehouse smaller or concurrency scale less. If you are NOT meeting your SLA

-----
This section is slightly different than the main cost allocation section below. Instead of aggregating costs at the unique query statement (query signature) level, it aggregates query statements (not unique) at the user level. It aims to answer the question of "of all the statements being executed, how much relative warehouse usage is being used by each user?"

widget.name: 2c0b34c8
widget.textbox_spec:
## Warehouse Performance - Data Scanning & Disk Spilling Metrics
Data Scanned helps understand how much data queries are reading - this is a decent proxy for warehouse size. Disk Spilling (both frequency and amount) is a clear metrics that helps track the amount of available memory in a cluster relative to the amount of data that needs to be processed in a given query.

##### Best Practices: 
Spilling to disk occasionally is completely fine, but when this happens consistently and the data volume of spilling is high (many many GBs/TBs), then it becomes highly likely that a larger warehouse is more performant AND cost effective.  When the % of queries spilling to disk increases, that is a clear sign the warehouse should be larger.
